  "texts": [
    "To measure the accuracy of a predictor, we defined the AUPR ratio as the ratio of the AUPR of a method to that of a random predictor.",
    "For a random predictor, the AUPR equals the fraction of positive samples in the dataset.",
    "The AUPR ratio is defined as",
    ", representing the fold change of the accuracy of a predictor compared to the random prediction.",
    "We propose a method to integrate GWAS summary statistics data and cell type-specific GRNs to identify the relevant cell types, key TFs and sub-GRNs responsible for GWAS variants."
